    "ConName": "Hourly",
    "TimeEntryDate": "2025-11-20",
    "Title": "RE: Phone issues",
    "TimeDiff": "- \n1.33 hrs",
    "Notes": "<p>Call received from Nathan. Requested him to create a remote session the 3cx system. Once the session has been created then setup a new session group for client and install the myremote on the server. After logged into the server with client and investigate the call flow issue with him. During the investigation found the following.</p><ol style=\"margin-top:0in;\" type=\"1\"><li data-list=\"0\" data-level=\"1\" style=\"color:#215E99;tab-stops:list .5in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Inter;\">The PBX is running on a Windows 10 machine, which is      now end-of-life (EOL).</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Inter;\"><br />We recommend upgrading the operating system to Windows 11 or a supported      Windows Server OS.</span></li><li data-list=\"0\" data-level=\"1\" style=\"color:#215E99;tab-stops:list .5in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Inter;\">Multiple devices were attempting to authenticate      against the PBX,</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Inter;\">&nbsp;which caused the system      to blacklist several IPs. We have removed those entries for now and will      continue monitoring in case anything similar occurs again.</span></li><li data-list=\"0\" data-level=\"1\" style=\"color:#215E99;tab-stops:list .5in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Inter;\">There are pending updates for the 3CX application.</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Inter;\"><br />We will schedule the maintenance tonight after 9:00 PM and will update you      once the maintenance is completed.</span></li><li data-list=\"0\" data-level=\"1\" style=\"color:#215E99;tab-stops:list .5in;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Inter;\">One 3CX service was stuck in a 'Starting' state,</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Inter;\">&nbsp;which may also have contributed to the inbound call issue. We rebooted the      server to resolve this.</span></li><p>&nbsp;</p><p>After that the call flow issue was fixed and they were able to make inbound and outbound calls.</p></ol>",
